@page "/reports"

<PageTitle>Reports</PageTitle>

<h1>Test Reports</h1>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <h5>Reports Coming Soon</h5>
    <p>
        The reports section will allow you to browse historical test results, 
        download evidence packs, and analyze test analytics. This feature is 
        currently under development.
    </p>
    
    <h6>Planned Features:</h6>
    <ul>
        <li>Browse completed test runs</li>
        <li>Download HTML, JSON, and JUnit reports</li>
        <li>View evidence packages (screenshots, DOM snapshots, logs)</li>
        <li>Test analytics and trends</li>
        <li>Healing suggestions and locator health</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>
        For now, you can access reports through the API endpoints directly or 
        view active run details in the <a href="/runs">Active Runs</a> section.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>API Endpoints</h3>
        <p>You can access reports programmatically using these endpoints:</p>
        <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li><code>GET /api/reports/{runId}?format=html</code> - HTML Report</li>
            <li><code>GET /api/reports/{runId}?format=json</code> - JSON Report</li>
            <li><code>GET /api/reports/{runId}?format=junit</code> - JUnit XML</li>
            <li><code>GET /api/reports/{runId}/evidence-pack</code> - Evidence ZIP</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>CLI Commands</h3>
        <p>Generate and view reports using the command line:</p>
        <pre><code>ai-agent report --runId &lt;runId&gt; --format html --open</code></pre>
        <pre><code>ai-agent report --runId &lt;runId&gt; --format json</code></pre>
        <pre><code>ai-agent report --runId &lt;runId&gt; --format junit</code></pre>
    </div>
</div>